rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Date Manufactured

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an individual aircraft to the date of the first flight of the aircraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: First Flight

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that sells, rents and/or leases airplanes and/or helicopters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Dealer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all aircraft designers. These are the agents that conduct the research and design of aircraft and spacecraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Designer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an aircraft designer to a model created by the designer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Models Designed

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of aircraft engines. These are the engines used as parts in mso:aviation.aircraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Engine Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating an aircraft engine type to an aircraft model in which the engine type is included.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all aircraft lines. Aircraft lines are the families of aircraft that share commonalities. For example, the company Airbus offers a line of aircraft called the A340, which contains four models the A340-200, the A340-300, the A340-500, and the A340-600.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a line of aircraft to one of the models in the product line, e.g. it relates the A340 family of aircraft offered by the Airbus company to the A340-200 model.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Models In Line

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A business that services and/or repairs airplanes and/or helicopters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Maintenance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of companies that construct aircraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Manufacturer

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an aircraft manufacturer to one of the models constructed by the manufacturer.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft Models Manufactured

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description:
Primary entity representing the collection of all aircraft models. These are models of both manned and unmanned machines capable of atmospheric flight. Sets of mso:aviation.aircraft_model with common characteristics make up mso:aviation.aircraft_lines.
Things that are an Aircraft Model:
## Models of fixed-wing aircraft such as airplanes and gliders (Concorde, De Havilland Express, Aichi B7A, Junkers Ju 390).
## Models of lighter-than-air aircraft such as airships and balloons (e.g. Hindenberg class airship, Skyship 600, SVAM CA-80).
## Models of rotary-wing aircraft such as autogyros, gyrodynes and helicopters (e.g. PZL SW-4 , Aerospatiale Puma, Fairey FB 1 Gyrodyne).
Things that are NOT an Aircraft Model:
## Instances of a particular model of aircraft (e.g. Enola Gay, Hemisphere Dancer, Spirit of Dubai) Use the mso:aviation.aircraft type for these.
## One-of-a-kind aircraft (e.g. R100, Meckler-Allen 1912 Biplane, Rigault RP.01B) Use mso:aviation.aircraft for these.
## Aircraft engines (e.g. Kuznetsov NK-12, CFM International CFM56, Pratt Whitney F135). Use mso:aviation.aircraft_engine_type for these.
## Rocket ships and satellites (e.g. UoSat OSCAR 9, Space Shuttle Discovery, Nozomi) Use mso:spaceflight.spacecraft for these.
## Munitions that travel through air using rocket thrust such as unguided missiles and rockets (e.g. UGM 133 Trident II, Exocet, RS-82 Rocket).
## Aircraft manufacturers and designers (e.g. Boeing Commercial Airplanes, Nakajima Aircraft Company, Sukhoi).
## Airlines (e.g. Air Namibia, Spanair, All Nippon Airways) Use mso:aviation.aircraft_line for these.
##General types of aircraft like 'Monoplane' and 'Unmanned aerial vehicle'. These are instances of mso:aviation.aircraft_type.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all airlines. Airlines are the companies that provide air transport services for passengers and freight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Accidents

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property linking an airline to information about the airports used by the airline.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Alliance

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates an airline to a number indicating how many aircraft are owned by the airline.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property relating an airline to the number of airports served by the airline.

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates the runway to its distance in meters above Mean Sea Level at the end of the runway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Elevation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a runway to the location at the end of the runway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: End Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a runway to the total length of the runway in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Length

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates the runway to its distance in meters above Mean Sea Level at the beginning of the runway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Elevation

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a runway to the location at the beginning of the runway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Start Location

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that relates a runway to the width of the runway in meters.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Width

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all runway surfaces. These are the materials like concrete or gravel that cover the runway.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airport Runway Surface

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all airport terminals. Terminals are the buildings at airports where passengers transfer between ground transportation and the facilities that allow them to board and disembark from aircraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airport Terminal

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property that relates an airport terminal to the airport that includes it.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airport

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of airport types. Important instances include 'international', 'military', and 'commercial'.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airport Type
Aviation incident/aircraft relationship
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This relationship type is not needed, because its properties duplicate properties on aviation.airliner_accident. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:aviation.airliner_accident]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The model of (one of) the aircraft involved in this incident. Note that this should be a model, such as Boeing 747 or Sopwith Camel.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of crew on this flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Crew

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The airport (helipad, carrier, etc.) to which the aircraft was headed.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flight destination

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The airport (helipad, carrier, etc.) from which the aircraft took off.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flight origin

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The number of passengers on this flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Passengers

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The total number of passengers and crew of this aircraft who survived this incident. (Note that this is distinct from the \"total survivors\" property of Aviation Incident, which is the sum of survivors of all aircraft involved.)
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Survivors

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The tail number (if any) of this aircraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Tail number

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all waypoints. Waypoints are the reference points in physical space that are used for navigation.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aviation Waypoint

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that links an aviation waypoint to a standard descriptor for its classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Waypoint Type
Cargo moved by year
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This relationship type is not needed. Use measurement_unit.dated_float as the expected type of aviation.airport.cargo_by_year. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:measurement_unit.dated_float]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Comparable Aircraft Relationship
rdf:Description.mso:type.type.deprecation_info: This relationship type is unnecessary. The property aviation.aircraft_model.comparable_aircraft should point directly to aviation.aircraft_model. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Aircraft
rdf:Description.mso:type.property.deprecation_info: This relationship type and its property are unnecessary. The property aviation.aircraft_model.comparable_aircraft should point directly to aviation.aircraft_model. DeprecatedBy:[REDMOND\ianiles] Successor:[mso:aviation.aircraft_model.comparable_aircraft ]

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A preference of a person regarding departure times, return times, airlines, and other things.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flight Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the airline that is preferred by the given person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline Flight Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the beginning of the preferred time frame for a departure flight by the given person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Departure Begin Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the end of the preferred time frame for a departure flight by the given person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Departure End Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of cuisine that is preferred by the given person while flying.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline Meal Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the person who has the given flight preferences.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Person with Flight Preferences

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the beginning of the preferred time frame for a return flight by the given person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Return Begin Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the end of the preferred time frame for a return flight by the given person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Return End Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the type of airline seating that is preferred by the given person.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline Seating Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A property that specifies the number of stops preferred by the given person for a flight.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Flight Stops Preference

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Two-letter codes assigned by the International Air Transport Association to airlines. Note that these codes are not ncessarily unique.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: IATA Airline Designator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a two-letter code assigned by the International Air Transport Association to the given airline. Note that these codes are not ncessarily unique.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Three-letter codes assigned by the International Civil Aviation Organization to airlines. These codes are unique to each airline.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: ICAO airline designator

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a three-letter codes assigned by the International Civil Aviation Organization to the given airline. Note that these codes are unique to each airline.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all pilots. Pilots are those people actively involved in flying an aircraft.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pilot

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Property relating an mso:aviation.pilot to the mso:aviation.aircraft_model the pilot is known for piloting.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Pilots Model

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: The type of ticket issued by the airline, viz. discounted, full-fare, round-trip, and one-way.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Airline Ticket Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: Primary entity representing the collection of all types of waypoints. These are the types of navigation aids used by pilots.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Waypoint Type

rdf:Description.mso:type.object.description: A virtual property relating a standard classification of waypoints to a waypoint in this classification.
rdf:Description.mso:type.object.name: Waypoints of this Type
